---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BookLayout from '../../layouts/BookLayout.astro';
import { buildToc } from '../../lib/toc';
import ErrorBudgetDashboard from '../../components/ErrorBudgetDashboard.astro';

const toc = buildToc(await getCollection('book'));
---

<BookLayout title="Error-budget dashboard" toc={toc}>
  <h1>Error-budget dashboard</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    The Ch. 31 worked error budget, made live. Position error is the root-sum-square
    of three independent <strong>error classes</strong> (Ch. 25) — stochastic
    (the CRLB), deterministic (tolerance ⊕ calibration residual), and environmental
    (post-compensation distortion) — and the balance between them <em>changes with
    where you are in the volume</em>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The stacked bars show the budget at near, mid, and far positions. The lesson the
    book repeats falls straight out of the picture: across most of the volume the
    tracker's own noise is <em>not</em> the limit — calibration and distortion are —
    so the high-value engineering is there, not in a quieter amplifier. Only at the
    far edge does the z⁴ CRLB take over, and only there do generator moment and
    sensor area-turns (the eq. 8.1 levers) buy accuracy.
  </p>
  <ErrorBudgetDashboard />
</BookLayout>
